25:28.354 --> 25:45.439
Then I looked and I heard around the throne and the living creatures and the elders and the voice of many angels numbering myriads of myriads and thousands of thousands saying with a loud voice worthy is the lamb who was slain to receive power and wealth and wisdom and might and honor and glory and blessing.

25:46.181 --> 25:57.938
Then I heard every creature in heaven and on earth and under the earth and in the sea and all that is in them saying to him who sits on the throne and to the lamb be blessing and honor and glory and might.

25:58.210 --> 25:59.471
forever and ever.

26:00.332 --> 26:02.114
And the four living creatures said, Amen.

26:02.795 --> 26:07.699
And the elders fell down and worshiped.

26:07.719 --> 26:07.819
Amen.

26:07.840 --> 26:08.040
Amen.

26:12.704 --> 26:17.149
If it wasn't for sin, we wouldn't need His word.

26:18.670 --> 26:20.892
We would just be worshiping.

26:20.912 --> 26:23.535
We would just be worshiping God like the angels and all the saints.

26:24.416 --> 26:26.578
It would just be us worshiping God all the time.

26:26.914 --> 26:31.620
Yet the sin that we have in our lives and before us requires that we have an outline.

26:31.940 --> 26:33.742
God's saying, here's what I'm expecting of you.

26:33.782 --> 26:34.704
Here's what I need you to do.

26:34.784 --> 26:35.925
Here's what I need you to walk in.

26:36.145 --> 26:37.247
Here's how I need you to do it.

26:38.508 --> 26:41.732
And like that buffet line, we go, I'll do that, but I won't do this.

26:42.413 --> 26:43.835
And I'll do that, but I won't do this.

26:45.257 --> 26:51.705
Or what if our moral compass and the way that we view things isn't the way that he sees it?

26:52.265 --> 26:56.050
And so when he speaks to us through his scripture and it doesn't align with our view of it,

26:56.546 --> 26:58.368
We go, I don't know if I subscribe to that.

26:59.949 --> 27:01.271
That's not what he's calling us to.

27:03.633 --> 27:11.160
So I'm constantly challenged when I open the pages of truth and it speaks to my heart and it convicts me and I go, I can't do this on my own.

27:11.200 --> 27:12.281
So Holy Spirit help.

27:20.149 --> 27:23.972
My prayer for our church is that we would cry out to the Holy Spirit help.

27:25.213 --> 27:25.874
We need you.

27:26.882 --> 27:27.723
I need you to come.

27:27.743 --> 27:29.125
I need you to fill my life.

27:29.366 --> 27:37.418
I want to experience Christ.

27:37.438 --> 27:42.946
I want to walk it out with love and the fruit of the Spirit.

27:44.308 --> 27:52.661
And so our barometer needs to be, am I walking out my life, my circumstances, my engagements, my interactions, my relationships in the power of the Spirit?

27:52.721 --> 27:55.986
And the barometer for that is, do I demonstrate the fruit of the Spirit?

27:57.922 --> 27:59.604
Was my action kind?

28:02.306 --> 28:04.848
Was it gentle that I love?

28:05.769 --> 28:06.470
Was I patient?

28:08.011 --> 28:11.515
I can tell you, as a dad, sometimes I'm not.

28:11.535 --> 28:13.957
But I want to be, I want to walk it out like Christ would.

28:14.778 --> 28:16.339
I want my kids to see Christ in me.

28:16.359 --> 28:17.821
I want my wife to see Christ in me.

28:18.201 --> 28:22.965
I want the church, our body here, to see Christ in me, not so that I can boast.

28:23.206 --> 28:24.827
But if I'm going to boast, I want to boast in Him.

28:25.087 --> 28:27.890
It's Him working in and through me so that they

28:28.130 --> 28:29.272
can see his glory.

28:35.682 --> 28:40.028
I share these things with conviction and passion because I don't want you to miss the invitation.

28:41.951 --> 28:43.514
I know what I've experienced in my life.

28:46.638 --> 28:48.802
And there's been hard times and there's been beautiful times.

28:49.983 --> 28:51.666
But in all of them, when he's

28:51.778 --> 28:53.340
Made this invitation to me.

28:53.600 --> 29:05.092
I've either said yes I want you to be a part of this invitation or I want to be a part of this party that you have Or no, I don't subscribe to that and I can tell you when I've said I don't subscribe to that It's not been great.

29:05.912 --> 29:19.346
It's been pretty miserable And even in the even in the sorrow filled hard difficult times of life When I just didn't know how I was gonna come out of that valley or that pit

29:19.842 --> 29:26.450
But I invited him into that circumstance and he said, I want to love you in this and I want you to know that you are my prized possession.

29:28.052 --> 29:31.656
I can tell you that joy that's unspeakable and full of glory.

29:32.077 --> 29:32.898
I've experienced that.

29:35.040 --> 29:35.281
How?

29:35.901 --> 29:37.603
The Holy Spirit came in and he did a work.

29:37.683 --> 29:38.504
He transformed me.

29:41.428 --> 29:42.369
I want that for all of you.

29:42.770 --> 29:46.814
Whatever circumstance you bring to the table today, he wants to sit down.

29:46.975 --> 29:49.778
Louis Giglio says, he wants to sit down at the table

29:49.954 --> 29:51.696
that He has prepared for you.

29:55.001 --> 29:58.565
He wants to commune with you, Louis Giglio says, I love that.

30:00.468 --> 30:02.010
And that brings us back to Revelation 21.

30:02.671 --> 30:06.336
The dwelling place of God is among us.

30:09.039 --> 30:13.165
And it's not the distinction between that God is in you when you invite Christ into your life.

30:13.185 --> 30:14.126
He certainly is.

30:15.648 --> 30:18.192
But when two or three gather together, he is there in the midst of them.

30:18.512 --> 30:19.954
He is their complimentary.

30:24.386 --> 30:28.390
I want us to experience new revelation in Christ.

30:28.831 --> 30:31.934
I want us to experience His character and His nature.

30:32.615 --> 30:33.296
How do we do that?

30:34.317 --> 30:36.219
We open up the books and the pages of truth.

30:37.740 --> 30:38.942
We sing worship songs.

30:40.043 --> 30:46.250
And as we sing before Him, as we bow our hearts before Him, He reveals Himself to us.

30:50.054 --> 30:53.938
These songs that we sing, hymns, songs, spiritual songs,

30:54.402 --> 31:02.373
are all points in people's lives over generations and generations of people realizing the revelation of Christ in their life.

31:05.337 --> 31:07.600
So we're gonna sing a couple more choruses and I wanna celebrate.

31:08.081 --> 31:11.025
I wanna celebrate with you and I wanna bring glory and honor to God.

31:11.345 --> 31:14.329
And so before we sing these choruses, I want you to search your heart.

31:17.514 --> 31:23.442
He has a future hope for us indeed, but he wants us to experience him here.

31:23.714 --> 31:33.323
And now, and we get to walk out this rich, beautiful life with Him and journey with Him if we will respond to His invitation and say, yes.

31:38.007 --> 31:43.553
So this morning, if you've never made that proclamation over your life, Jesus, I want you to come.

31:43.693 --> 31:44.754
I know John shared it earlier.

31:45.354 --> 31:46.275
Maybe you're resisting it.

31:46.335 --> 31:47.196
I'm just going to share it again.

31:47.717 --> 31:51.040
All you have to say is, Jesus, I want you to be Lord of my life.

31:51.420 --> 31:53.522
I want you to come and I want you to fill

31:53.698 --> 31:54.739
my life.

31:55.720 --> 31:57.603
I want to put you over all things.

31:58.484 --> 31:59.885
I'm not asking you to raise your hand.

31:59.945 --> 32:01.006
This is between you and him.

32:01.447 --> 32:07.814
Your baptism, I look forward to when you get to publicly profess that you made Jesus Lord of your life.

32:09.436 --> 32:11.138
I look forward to celebrating with you on that day.

32:13.161 --> 32:17.906
But if you do make that decision today, your life will never be the same.

32:19.394 --> 32:25.361
Maybe there's those of us who say, yeah, I've called him Lord before, but like in Matthew, I don't do the will of the Father.

32:25.401 --> 32:27.003
I'm not being sanctified.

32:27.363 --> 32:28.905
I'm not walking in obedience.

32:30.787 --> 32:31.829
What does that look like for you?

32:33.511 --> 32:34.792
So surrender that to him today.

32:34.852 --> 32:39.598
If that's speaking to your heart, say, Holy Spirit, I need you to come in and I need you to transform my life.

32:39.918 --> 32:41.940
I haven't given this thing over to you yet.

32:42.461 --> 32:43.462
And I know that I need to.

32:45.625 --> 32:46.706
I don't want to be.

32:47.938 --> 32:53.306
On that day where he returns and he says, depart from me, I never knew you.

32:55.670 --> 32:56.652
And I don't want that for you.

32:59.636 --> 33:02.701
So is it just a posture of worship and a heart of worship?

33:03.462 --> 33:07.669
You can feel free to sit, feel free to stand or move about the space.

33:07.689 --> 33:12.516
But I just, I want to give him praise and honor his name.

33:12.536 --> 33:16.242
And it's a chorus that we've sang together before.

33:18.082 --> 33:21.306
Jess, you can come back up and Sam, you can come back up.

33:21.326 --> 33:22.367
We're gonna sing two choruses.

33:22.447 --> 33:23.288
Jesus, we love you.

33:25.872 --> 33:27.033
And then only you are holy.

33:27.073 --> 33:35.864
Thanks for listening to the Crossway Christian Church's Millford campus sermon podcast.

33:36.164 --> 33:43.413
If you'd like to plug into the life of our community or have any questions that we might be able to answer, visit our website at crosswaycc.org to connect with us.

33:43.854 --> 33:45.136
Until next time, we can be with you.

33:45.176 --> 33:47.058
May the Lord bless you and keep you.

